        {
            "name": "Stripe Webhook",
            "description": "‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: Webhook endpoint requires real Stripe signature verification.\n\nFor testing, use Stripe Test Mode:\n1. Use test keys (sk_test_..., pk_test_..., whsec_test_...)\n2. Use Stripe CLI or Stripe Dashboard to send test events\n3. The webhook will work exactly as in production\n\nTo go live, simply swap environment variables to live keys - no code changes needed.",
            "item": [{
                    "name": "üìñ How to Test Webhooks",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stripe/webhook",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "stripe", "webhook"]
                        },
                        "description": "## Testing Webhooks with Stripe Test Mode\n\n### Option 1: Stripe CLI (Recommended for Local Testing)\n\n1. **Install Stripe CLI**:\n   ```bash\n   # macOS\n   brew install stripe/stripe-cli/stripe\n   \n   # Windows\n   # Download from https://github.com/stripe/stripe-cli/releases\n   ```\n\n2. **Login to Stripe**:\n   ```bash\n   stripe login\n   ```\n\n3. **Forward webhooks to your local server**:\n   ```bash\n   stripe listen --forward-to localhost:3000/api/stripe/webhook\n   ```\n   This will output a webhook signing secret (whsec_...). Add it to your .env as STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET.\n\n4. **Trigger test events**:\n   ```bash\n   stripe trigger checkout.session.completed\n   stripe trigger customer.subscription.created\n   stripe trigger customer.subscription.updated\n   stripe trigger customer.subscription.deleted\n   ```\n\n### Option 2: Stripe Dashboard (For Vercel/Production Testing)\n\n1. **Go to Stripe Dashboard** ‚Üí Developers ‚Üí Webhooks\n\n2. **Add endpoint** (for testing on Vercel):\n   - Endpoint URL: `https://logofy-api.vercel.app/api/stripe/webhook`\n   - Events to send:\n     - `checkout.session.completed`\n     - `customer.subscription.created`\n     - `customer.subscription.updated`\n     - `customer.subscription.deleted`\n\n3. **Copy the Signing Secret** (whsec_...) and add to your Vercel environment variables as `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`\n\n4. **Send test events** from the webhook endpoint page using \"Send test webhook\"\n\n### Option 3: Real Test Payments\n\n1. Use test card: `4242 4242 4242 4242`\n2. Complete a checkout session using the billing endpoints\n3. Stripe will automatically send webhook events\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n**For Testing (Test Mode):**\n```\nSTRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...\nSTRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...\nSTRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_test_...\n```\n\n**For Production (Live Mode):**\n```\nSTRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...\nSTRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_...\nSTRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_live_...\n```\n\n**No code changes needed** - just swap the keys!"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "‚ö†Ô∏è Note: Cannot Test Directly in Postman",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            },
                            {
                                "key": "stripe-signature",
                                "value": "",
                                "description": "This header is automatically generated by Stripe and cannot be manually created. You must use Stripe CLI or Stripe Dashboard to send properly signed webhooks."
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"id\": \"evt_test\",\n    \"object\": \"event\",\n    \"type\": \"checkout.session.completed\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"object\": {}\n    }\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stripe/webhook",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "stripe", "webhook"]
                        },
                        "description": "‚ùå **This request will fail** because Postman cannot generate valid Stripe signatures.\n\nStripe webhook signatures are cryptographically signed using:\n- The raw request body\n- A timestamp\n- The webhook signing secret\n\n**You cannot manually create valid signatures.**\n\n‚úÖ **Use one of these methods instead:**\n1. Stripe CLI (see \"üìñ How to Test Webhooks\" request)\n2. Stripe Dashboard \"Send test webhook\"\n3. Complete a real test payment with test card 4242 4242 4242 4242"
                    }
                }
            ]
